    <description>

      <levelledPara id="desc-020-020-001">
        <title>General</title>
        <para>This data module describes the <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Distribution System</emphasis> of the AMPEL360e eWTW ECS, aligned to ATLAS node 020-020 and ATA 21-20. The distribution system routes conditioned air from the air conditioning packs to the cabin, cockpit, galley areas and equipment bays.</para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara id="desc-020-020-002">
        <title>Distribution Architecture</title>
        <para>The eWTW distribution system uses a zoned architecture to control airflow independently in different areas of the aircraft:</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem><para>Forward cabin zone (rows 1–NN, forward galley).</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Mid cabin zone (main passenger area).</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Aft cabin zone (aft galley, lavatories).</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Cockpit and avionics zone.</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Equipment bay and cargo bay conditioning.</para></listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara id="desc-020-020-003">
        <title>Key Components</title>
        <para>Major components of the distribution subsystem include:</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem><para>Primary and secondary mixing manifolds.</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Zone trim air valves for temperature trimming.</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Cabin air supply ducts (overhead, underfloor).</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Individual Air Units (IAU) for passenger overhead supply.</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Recirculation fans and HEPA filtration units.</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Equipment bay air supply and return ducts.</para></listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara id="desc-020-020-004">
        <title>Recirculation and Air Quality</title>
        <para>The eWTW ECS uses a mixed fresh-air and recirculated-air strategy. Recirculated air passes through HEPA filters before re-entering the cabin. The fresh-air fraction is maintained at or above the minimum required by cabin air quality standards. Air quality monitoring sensors are integrated with the ECS monitoring system (see DMC-AMPEL360E-EWTW-020-080-00A-040A-D).</para>
      </levelledPara>

    </description>
